<emphasis id="B901853DFFB7CC70A38CBCF0FEF2FA04" bold="true" box="[199,308,1415,1441]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFFB7CC70A20FBCF0FDCCFA04" authorityName="Kohl" authorityYear="1905" box="[324,522,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoniger">
<emphasis id="B901853DFFB7CC70A20FBCF0FDCCFA04" box="[324,522,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Ophion rufoniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="134E45AAFFB7CC70A152BCF0FD02FA04" box="[537,708,1415,1441]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1391,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-24@34.[151,1391,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 16. A) Ophion rufoniger Kohl, ♀, mesosoma and head, lateral view; B) Ophion rufoniger, head of ♀, lateral view; C) Ophion semipullatus Kokujev, mesosoma and head of ♀, lateral view; D) Ophion semipullatus, head of ♀, lateral view; E) Ophion semipullatus, head of ♀, anterior view; F) Ophion rufoniger, head of ♀, anterior view. Photos: Niklas Johansson." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225688/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Figs 16A‒B, F</figureCitation>
) was described from 
<collectingRegion id="49B197CDFFB7CC70A0F2BCF0FBCBFA04" box="[953,1037,1415,1441]" country="Azerbaijan" name="Goygol" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Goygol</collectingRegion>
in Northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F36219BFFFB7CC70A79ABCF0FA8AFA04" box="[1233,1356,1415,1441]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE424DEFFB7CC70A617BCF0FF15FA60" author="Kohl, F. F." pageId="33" pageNumber="184" pagination="220 - 246" refId="ref32257" refString="Kohl, F. F. (1905) Hymenopteren. In: Penther, A. &amp; Zederbauer, E. (Eds.), &quot; Ergebnisse einer naturwissenschaftlichen Reise zur Erdschias-Dagh (Kleinasien). &quot; Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museum in Wien, 20, pp. 220 - 246." type="journal article" year="1905">Kohl, 1905</bibRefCitation>
). It is a very rarely recorded species also known from 
<collectingCountry id="F36219BFFFB7CC70A016BCDCFC79FA60" box="[861,959,1451,1477]" name="Armenia" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Armenia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36219BFFFB7CC70A0B6BCDCFB9CFA60" box="[1021,1114,1451,1477]" name="Georgia" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Georgia</collectingCountry>
. The species is quite easily determined based on the buccate head and the dark reddish brown body with mainly black metasoma and legs. The depicted female specimen is from 
<collectingCountry id="F36219BFFFB7CC70A153BC84FDB4F9A8" box="[536,626,1523,1549]" name="Georgia" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and housed in OÖLM.
</paragraph>
